modules.description: Provides functions to traverse and modify abstract syntax trees generated by Clang, including node replacement, insertion, and deletion. Operates on structured representations of C/C++ code, such as expressions, statements, and declarations. Enables precise source-to-source transformations, like inline function expansion or macro substitution.

Constructs and manipulates binary operations, integer literals, and statement sequences in C ASTs, with type-aware creation of integer expressions. Operates on Clang AST nodes, including expressions, statements, and declarations. Used to rewrite arithmetic operations, generate constant expressions, and restructure control flow blocks.
